promptsTts.value: To check your balance related items press 1.  To make a payment on your fiber service press 2.  To restart your router remotely press 3.  To set up new service or to speak to a representative,  press 4. For technical support press 5.

<speak>Your account is showing a past due amount of {{pastDue}} which is due at this time. Your account is subject to disconnection on the past due amount. The current balance for this account is <say-as interpret-as="currency">{{balance}}</say-as>. Your last payment of <say-as interpret-as="currency">{{lastPayment}}</say-as> was received on {{lastPaymentDate}}.</speak>
To make a payment, press 1. To return to the main menu, press 9. to speak with an agent, press 0.

<speak>The current balance for this account is <say-as interpret-as="currency">{{balance}}</say-as>. The amount due is listed as <say-as interpret-as="currency">{{amountDue}}</say-as> and is due on {{dueDate}}. Your last payment of <say-as interpret-as="currency">{{lastPayment}}</say-as> was received on {{lastPaymentDate}}.   </speak>
<speak>Your current balance is<say-as interpret-as="currency"> {{balance}}</say-as>, which includes a past due amount of {{pastDue}} which is due at this time.</speak>
To pay your current balance, press 1.  To pay a different amount, press 2.
<speak>Your current balance is <say-as interpret-as="currency"> {{balance}}</say-as></speak>
If you would like to make a payment with a checking account, press 1. To make a payment with a credit card, press 2. For assistance in making a payment over the phone, press 0
Please say or enter the amount to be paid in dollars and cents. For example, ten dollars would be spoken or entered as one zero zero zero.

promptsTts.value: <speak>Your payment in the amount of <say-as interpret-as="currency">${{amount}}</say-as> has been accepted. The confirmation code is <say-as interpret-as="characters">{{AuthorizationCode}}</say-as>.</speak>

Please enter the credit card number
Please enter the four digit expiration in the format two digit month and two digit year.
Please enter the three or four digit CVV code
Please enter the five digit postal code.

Enter the routing number
